text: Raden Panji Mohammad Noer (January 13, 1918 in Sampang Regency – April 16, 2010) was the Indonesian Governor of East Java from 1967 to 1976. He was also ambassador to France from 1976 to 1980.Muhammad Noer Dies ==References== Category:1918 births Category:2010 deaths Category:People from Sampang Regency Category:Governors of East Java Category:Ambassadors of Indonesia to France
